entries.npc_dropoff_2: Good job getting me here. This is a rough place.
entries.npc_takeme_2: I'm glad to see you. For a moment I thought somebody was after me.
entries.npc_breech_2: Are you here to bring me to the CSA Deputy Viceprex?
entries.dontknowyou_2: I'm waiting for someone else to meet me.
entries.otherescort_2: I'm expecting to meet somebody else here.
entries.npc_failure_2: I hate it when unforeseen problems arise.
entries.npc_noloc_2: Let me call our associates on the other end and make sure everything is clear. See me in a few minutes.
entries.npc_work_2: Haven't you even left yet? Get moving.
entries.npc_reward_2: I hope you didn't have too much trouble. I'll take care of things from here.
entries.npc_backtowork_2: Did you want this job or not?
entries.npc_4_2: A temporary reduction of shipping rates, as well as other good and valuable considerations for which reciprocal benefits would manifest in due time for those individuals vested in the -- I shouldn't bore you with details. Will you do it?
entries.npc_3_2: I'll look for someone else to help me.
entries.npc_2_2: These trips aren't all that uncommon. It's one of the perks when you're a union rep who works with the CSA. Try not to draw attention when you escort him back. The fewer folks who know he's here, the better.
entries.npc_1_2: I'm glad you're here. We've had one of the spice mining union representatives quietly brought to Corellia to negotiate a special deal. Would you mind escorting him here safely?
entries.player_3_1: What are you hiring me to do exactly?
entries.player_sorry_1: I'll keep working on the mission.
entries.player_reset_1: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.notit_1: That's not the disk I was told to expect. Look again.
entries.gotowork_1: What did you do with the disk you were supposed to bring me?
entries.npc_smuggle_1: You tell them I'll take care of this right away.
entries.npc_breech_1: Do you have something for me from the Deputy Viceprex?
entries.dontknowyou_1: I'm waiting for someone else, friend, sorry.
entries.otherescort_1: I'm waiting for someone else, friend, sorry.
entries.npc_failure_1: Ran in to difficulties along the way, did you?
entries.npc_noloc_1: I need to contact our slicer and see where he wants the drop. Check back in a few minutes after I take care of that.
entries.npc_work_1: Have you dropped off that disk yet? It's something you shouldn't wait to do.
entries.npc_reward_1: Wonderful. Come back and see me later. The CSA may be able to offer you more work.
entries.npc_backtowork_1: Are you going to make that delivery?
entries.npc_4_1: He's not the only one who can employ data slicers to alter records. I want you to take this datadisc to our slicer. Let's just say when he's finished, it won't be the Viceprex who looks like a fool. Will you do it?
entries.npc_3_1: Don't you have somewhere else to be?
entries.npc_2_1: Bring this disk to Reeve Taggart. He'll make some changes in this altered report and then upload it to where it belongs.
entries.npc_1_1: You want to work for the Corporate Sector Authority? One of the Viceprex's underlings has had data slicers alter shipping documents to make the Viceprex seem incompetent and corrupt. I need help with damage control. What do you say?
entries.npc_reset: I'll keep the job open for you in case you change your mind.
entries.cantwork: Finish up your current job and then see me about some work.
entries.next: Your services are very much appreciated. I don't have anything further for you right now. Perhaps you should speak with the Viceprex.
